modules.description: Applies a function to each element of a structure or pairs elements from two structures in parallel. Operates on parameterized container types, transforming or processing their contents. Used to generate new values from existing ones or perform side effects across paired collections.

Provides optimization routines using the L-BFGS algorithm, including gradient computation, line search, and convergence checks. Operates on numerical arrays and vectors of type `float array` or `Owl.Dense.Ndarray.t`. Used for training machine learning models and solving nonlinear optimization problems with large datasets.

Provides a set of operations for transforming and combining elements within parameterized data structures, including mapping over single structures and zipping pairs from two structures. Supports functions that generate new values or trigger side effects during traversal. Examples include applying a mathematical function to each element of a vector or combining corresponding elements from two arrays. Key data types include generic containers and paired elements, with operations focused on element-wise processing and aggregation.
